Tottenham Spurs on Saturday evening stunned English Premier League leader, Manchester City, with a 2-3 home defeat, throwing open the contest of the premiership title this season.
Harry Kane, England captain, scored two goals in the 3-2 away victory over Man. City at the Etihad.
Tottenham’s away victory halted City’s unbeaten run in 16 games.
Liverpool on Saturday defeated Norwich City 3-1 to stabilize their second position and chase for the number one position towards winning the premiership league title this season.
Liverpool will play Leeds United on Wednesday, and a victory in the game will narrow the gap with Man City.
Chelsea also beat Crystal Palace 0-1 in an away march on Saturday, trailing third on the league table.
